1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,626 --> 00:01:35,465
Buy three cases,

3
00:01:35,465 --> 00:01:36,226
and get a free case

4
00:01:36,226 --> 00:01:37,105
of bottled water.

5
00:01:37,646 --> 00:01:38,146
Yes.

6
00:01:38,146 --> 00:01:39,265
It's a great deal.

7
00:01:39,866 --> 00:01:40,825
So, three cases?

8
00:01:41,025 --> 00:01:41,545
Alright.

9
00:01:41,545 --> 00:01:42,586
Let me arrange it.

10
00:01:42,986 --> 00:01:44,025
Careful. It's heavy.

11
00:01:44,025 --> 00:01:44,825
Yes.

12
00:01:45,066 --> 00:01:46,146
Three cases of brandy.

13
00:01:46,146 --> 00:01:46,646
That's all.

14
00:01:47,265 --> 00:01:49,426
Mr. Liu, welcome to come again.

15
00:01:53,586 --> 00:01:54,626
How much is this wine?

16
00:01:55,066 --> 00:01:57,426
This one? It was originally 1,200.

17
00:01:58,185 --> 00:01:58,685
What?

18
00:01:59,105 --> 00:01:59,605
Sir.

19
00:02:00,105 --> 00:02:01,786
Did she give you a 5% discount

20
00:02:02,105 --> 00:02:03,946
for three cases of brandy?

21
00:02:04,586 --> 00:02:05,146
Yes.

22
00:02:05,545 --> 00:02:06,866
Look, this is Gennadiy.

23
00:02:07,706 --> 00:02:08,946
We're running a promotion,

24
00:02:09,066 --> 00:02:10,825
so I can give you a 10% discount.

25
00:02:11,705 --> 00:02:12,226
Let me look.

26
00:02:12,226 --> 00:02:14,466
Let me tell you, Gennadiy tastes better.

27
00:02:14,825 --> 00:02:16,385
And the brand is bigger too.

28
00:02:16,946 --> 00:02:18,585
But the Gennadiy is more expensive.

29
00:02:19,145 --> 00:02:20,786
I told you.
I'll give you a 10% discount.

30
00:02:20,786 --> 00:02:22,825
Actually, it's not much more expensive.

31
00:02:22,906 --> 00:02:23,626
Well,

32
00:02:23,825 --> 00:02:26,746
are you planning
to give this wine as a gift?

33
00:02:27,186 --> 00:02:27,825
Sure, so?

34
00:02:27,825 --> 00:02:31,105
So you need Gennadiy.
It's a well-known brand.

35
00:02:32,186 --> 00:02:32,985
But...

36
00:02:33,346 --> 00:02:35,226
How about this?

37
00:02:35,226 --> 00:02:35,746
Well,

38
00:02:37,385 --> 00:02:38,105
I can

39
00:02:38,105 --> 00:02:40,585
personally give you a wine set.

40
00:02:40,746 --> 00:02:42,105
It's worth over 3,000.

41
00:02:42,105 --> 00:02:43,506
And it's imported from Germany.

42
00:02:43,506 --> 00:02:44,385
This is between us.

43
00:02:44,385 --> 00:02:46,066
Please don't tell anyone else, okay?

44
00:02:47,746 --> 00:02:48,346
Alright then.

45
00:02:48,786 --> 00:02:49,585
I'll buy from you.

46
00:02:49,585 --> 00:02:50,466
Great, sir.

47
00:02:50,466 --> 00:02:51,746
You can leave the wine here.

48
00:02:51,746 --> 00:02:52,904
I'll go write you a receipt.

49
00:02:53,026 --> 00:02:54,506
Alright, I'll look around then.

50
00:02:54,506 --> 00:02:55,006
Okay.

51
00:02:59,226 --> 00:03:00,746
You're shameless!

52
00:03:01,026 --> 00:03:02,145
How could you do that?

53
00:03:02,585 --> 00:03:04,306
I spent over ten minutes
with the customer.

54
00:03:04,506 --> 00:03:05,786
Why did you steal my customer?

55
00:03:06,026 --> 00:03:08,105
The customer can buy wherever they want.

56
00:03:08,105 --> 00:03:09,105
Is there a problem?

57
00:03:09,226 --> 00:03:10,346
You're breaking the rules.

58
00:03:10,506 --> 00:03:13,066
In this line of work,
it's all about skill.

59
00:03:13,585 --> 00:03:14,506
Not about rules.

60
00:03:19,026 --> 00:03:20,626
Fine. Just wait.

61
00:03:21,425 --> 00:03:22,145
Ms. Zhao.

62
00:03:22,145 --> 00:03:22,825
Fang.

63
00:03:22,946 --> 00:03:24,385
I'm crashing into you!

64
00:03:24,385 --> 00:03:24,885
Watch out!

65
00:03:26,026 --> 00:03:27,105
- I'm killing you!
- Nuts!

66
00:03:28,385 --> 00:03:29,466
How dare you!

67
00:03:29,585 --> 00:03:30,946
You stole my customer!

68
00:03:30,946 --> 00:03:31,825
- Stop!
- Stop!

69
00:03:31,825 --> 00:03:32,746
Stop fighting!

70
00:03:32,946 --> 00:03:34,585
Stop fighting!

71
00:03:34,585 --> 00:03:35,865
I'll kick you to death!

72
00:03:36,226 --> 00:03:37,226
Are you nuts?

73
00:03:37,786 --> 00:03:39,466
Stop fighting! No fighting allowed here.

74
00:03:39,466 --> 00:03:41,265
Or we'll revoke your booth licenses.

75
00:03:41,265 --> 00:03:41,865
Stop!

76
00:03:41,865 --> 00:03:42,906
Revoke your licenses.

77
00:03:42,906 --> 00:03:44,425
I'll beat you to death.

78
00:03:44,466 --> 00:03:45,786
You think I don't dare?

79
00:03:45,786 --> 00:03:46,746
Calm down!

80
00:03:47,265 --> 00:03:48,466
Sorry about this.

81
00:03:48,466 --> 00:03:49,026
You just wait.

82
00:03:49,026 --> 00:03:49,526
What?

83
00:03:49,746 --> 00:03:50,585
Calm down!

84
00:03:50,865 --> 00:03:51,865
You just wait.

85
00:03:53,306 --> 00:03:54,466
Everyone, get out of here.

86
00:03:54,466 --> 00:03:55,186
- It's a mistake.
- Stop.

87
00:03:55,186 --> 00:03:56,145
Get out of here.

88
00:03:56,145 --> 00:03:56,985
- Sorry.
- Get out of here.

89
00:03:57,466 --> 00:03:58,985
Fortunately, it's just a bruise.

90
00:04:02,545 --> 00:04:04,145
I just felt a twinge in my waist.

91
00:04:05,585 --> 00:04:07,906
Fang, you're not young anymore.

92
00:04:08,746 --> 00:04:09,705
Don't be so aggressive.

93
00:04:10,066 --> 00:04:11,385
Be careful of retaliation.

94
00:04:11,746 --> 00:04:12,626
Retaliation?

95
00:04:12,746 --> 00:04:14,346
I should be the one seeking revenge.

96
00:04:23,746 --> 00:04:26,866
I'm sorry for causing trouble again.

97
00:04:29,585 --> 00:04:31,186
My boyfriend will pick me up soon.

98
00:04:31,465 --> 00:04:32,905
Isn't today the last day?

99
00:04:33,025 --> 00:04:33,866
Big sale.

100
00:04:35,306 --> 00:04:38,265
Don't be angry.
I won't cause you trouble anymore.

101
00:04:40,705 --> 00:04:42,145
Am I afraid of the trouble?

102
00:04:44,426 --> 00:04:45,546
I'm worried about you.

103
00:04:47,465 --> 00:04:49,186
I know you care about me the most.

104
00:04:51,025 --> 00:04:51,525
Okay.

105
00:04:52,385 --> 00:04:53,946
I'll get back to work then.

106
00:04:55,306 --> 00:04:56,585
Seriously, Fang?

107
00:04:56,746 --> 00:04:58,705
You're in this state
and still going to work?

108
00:04:58,905 --> 00:05:00,866
This little injury is nothing.

109
00:05:01,325 --> 00:05:01,825
Look,

110
00:05:01,825 --> 00:05:03,585
if I see Wilson's people again,
I'll fight.

111
00:05:05,145 --> 00:05:06,306
Tonight, it's so close

112
00:05:06,986 --> 00:05:07,866
to reaching 200,000.

113
00:05:11,345 --> 00:05:12,186
Go for it!

114
00:05:22,829 --> 00:05:27,394
=Episode 19=
(Foolish Innocence)

115
00:05:30,265 --> 00:05:32,866
So you're asking
about next month's exact sales figures?

116
00:05:32,866 --> 00:05:34,626
Yes, the more precise, the better.

117
00:05:34,825 --> 00:05:37,186
I think you can start
with the waitstaff you're close to.

118
00:05:37,186 --> 00:05:39,746
But make sure
their distributors never find out.

119
00:05:39,905 --> 00:05:40,666
Okay, got it.

120
00:05:41,025 --> 00:05:42,426
Anyway, this is pretty sensitive.

121
00:05:42,585 --> 00:05:44,626
I've heard
they often inflate sales numbers.

122
00:05:44,626 --> 00:05:46,546
- Sure, so we need to investigate.
- Count the bottles!

123
00:05:46,986 --> 00:05:47,905
Brilliant idea!

124
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:49,825
- Fa, you often go to the back door.
- Yes?

125
00:05:49,825 --> 00:05:50,825
- Count them then.
- Okay.

126
00:05:50,825 --> 00:05:51,506
Do it quietly.

127
00:05:51,626 --> 00:05:52,265
Alright.

128
00:05:55,025 --> 00:05:56,746
Have you told Fang about this?

129
00:05:57,066 --> 00:05:58,946
She is in a flagship store.

130
00:05:58,946 --> 00:06:00,705
If word gets out, it'll be trouble.

131
00:06:00,705 --> 00:06:02,385
If you were at Cocoon right now,

132
00:06:02,385 --> 00:06:03,946
I wouldn't dare ask you to investigate.

133
00:06:05,186 --> 00:06:07,626
If Shen Mo finds out, we're both dead.

134
00:06:09,746 --> 00:06:12,705
This task was only notified
to promoters individually,

135
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:14,265
not announced in the work group.

136
00:06:14,385 --> 00:06:15,465
Okay, I understand.

137
00:06:15,705 --> 00:06:16,825
Leave this to me.

138
00:06:16,905 --> 00:06:17,506
Good luck!

139
00:06:17,506 --> 00:06:18,265
We're heading out.

140
00:06:18,385 --> 00:06:19,025
- Okay.
- Bye.

141
00:06:19,025 --> 00:06:19,825
- Good luck!
- Got it.

142
00:06:19,825 --> 00:06:21,236
- Count on you.
- Stay in touch.

143
00:06:21,236 --> 00:06:22,025
Don't worry. Bye!

144
00:06:22,025 --> 00:06:23,025
Be careful on the road.

145
00:06:23,746 --> 00:06:24,585
Hurry up.

146
00:06:25,025 --> 00:06:25,825
Coming!

147
00:06:26,106 --> 00:06:27,145
Be careful.

148
00:06:28,705 --> 00:06:29,506
Leaving.

149
00:06:31,265 --> 00:06:31,986
Love you guys.

150
00:06:32,186 --> 00:06:35,345
Sir, our store seems busy.

151
00:06:35,825 --> 00:06:38,626
I bet we sell over 50 bottles
of brandy nightly.

152
00:06:38,746 --> 00:06:39,626
Not at all.

153
00:06:39,626 --> 00:06:42,265
Tonight's good sales are
because of your promotion.

154
00:06:42,585 --> 00:06:43,705
It doesn't often happen.

155
00:06:49,025 --> 00:06:51,825
Chen, you didn't sell many tonight.

156
00:06:52,946 --> 00:06:53,986
This is already good!

157
00:06:59,825 --> 00:07:03,866
Sir, how many do we usually sell
without promotions?

158
00:07:03,866 --> 00:07:05,746
About 30 bottles daily, normally.

159
00:07:05,946 --> 00:07:06,946
Last month was worse.

160
00:07:07,066 --> 00:07:09,265
We only sold about 750 bottles
of brandy in total.

161
00:07:09,626 --> 00:07:12,385
Gennadiy 25 did slightly better.

162
00:07:12,465 --> 00:07:13,506
Around 1,000 bottles.

163
00:07:14,145 --> 00:07:17,785
Last night was even worse.
I didn't sell ten bottles all night.

164
00:07:19,506 --> 00:07:20,426
I'm heading back.

165
00:07:20,705 --> 00:07:21,265
Go ahead.

166
00:07:23,626 --> 00:07:26,385
Excuse me, your drink. Enjoy.

167
00:07:26,626 --> 00:07:28,306
This limited edition Gennadiy 25

168
00:07:28,306 --> 00:07:29,946
is selling very well in-store.

169
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:32,746
Sir, take a look first.
I'll explain more later.

170
00:07:35,066 --> 00:07:36,385
Sold 55 bottles total last night.

171
00:07:45,634 --> 00:07:48,296
(Wang Hao, Sales Data Summary)

172
00:07:51,362 --> 00:07:53,416
(Zeng Zixuan, Sales Data Summary)

173
00:07:56,306 --> 00:07:58,506
(Got so much data this fast?)

174
00:08:01,306 --> 00:08:02,746
(My girls helped a lot!)

175
00:08:06,306 --> 00:08:09,066
The left side
is what distributors reported.

176
00:08:09,066 --> 00:08:10,186
The red on the right

177
00:08:10,186 --> 00:08:11,666
is from our people.

178
00:08:12,626 --> 00:08:13,946
Huge difference!

179
00:08:14,265 --> 00:08:15,306
Actual sales

180
00:08:15,306 --> 00:08:17,825
are 50 percent lower than projected.

181
00:08:19,866 --> 00:08:21,825
How many stores total?

182
00:08:22,626 --> 00:08:24,825
55 stores,
just a small portion of all stores.

183
00:08:25,066 --> 00:08:26,186
Oh, my God!

184
00:08:27,186 --> 00:08:28,345
50 percent!

185
00:08:29,186 --> 00:08:30,066
My God!

186
00:08:30,546 --> 00:08:32,946
Yes, for just one quarter, actually.

187
00:08:33,186 --> 00:08:35,386
It means at least 30 percent
of last year's total volume

188
00:08:35,386 --> 00:08:36,745
is still sitting

189
00:08:36,745 --> 00:08:38,705
in distributors' stock.

190
00:08:39,505 --> 00:08:40,946
With the market downturn,

191
00:08:41,186 --> 00:08:43,625
long-term distributors like Shen Mo

192
00:08:44,026 --> 00:08:46,306
could sell for one to two years

193
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:50,546
just from existing stock,
even without new products.

194
00:08:52,306 --> 00:08:53,105
I see.

195
00:08:54,825 --> 00:08:56,306
If there's nothing else,

196
00:08:57,186 --> 00:08:58,345
I'll head out now.

197
00:09:01,386 --> 00:09:02,186
Well done.

198
00:09:03,546 --> 00:09:04,306
It's a small case.

199
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:07,186
Bye.

200
00:09:24,386 --> 00:09:24,886
Bye.

201
00:09:26,426 --> 00:09:27,066
Beautiful.

202
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:30,505
Quite interesting.

203
00:09:30,505 --> 00:09:32,105
- Let's try.
- No.

204
00:09:32,865 --> 00:09:33,505
Alright.

205
00:09:42,186 --> 00:09:42,825
Thank you.

206
00:09:43,566 --> 00:09:44,066
Okay.

207
00:09:44,066 --> 00:09:44,566
This way.

208
00:09:45,736 --> 00:09:47,426
Hi, Mr. Shen.

209
00:09:48,266 --> 00:09:49,306
Long time no see.

210
00:09:52,426 --> 00:09:54,066
Barry just told me

211
00:09:54,345 --> 00:09:56,225
he visited some stores
in the East District.

212
00:09:56,705 --> 00:09:57,825
Less better than Cocoon.

213
00:09:58,306 --> 00:09:59,946
They're not even in the same league.

214
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:02,306
Those stores are just at this level,

215
00:10:02,705 --> 00:10:05,066
while the Cocoon is at a higher level.

216
00:10:07,266 --> 00:10:07,786
What's wrong?

217
00:10:09,505 --> 00:10:10,705
Mr. Shen,

218
00:10:10,705 --> 00:10:11,985
did something happen?

219
00:10:15,618 --> 00:10:17,768
What the heck?

220
00:10:19,010 --> 00:10:19,821
Darn you!

221
00:10:24,825 --> 00:10:25,465
Boss!

222
00:10:25,465 --> 00:10:27,906
Who told you
to mess with the retailers on your own?

223
00:10:27,906 --> 00:10:29,946
You actually bypassed the distributors

224
00:10:29,946 --> 00:10:30,946
and checked their books?

225
00:10:30,946 --> 00:10:32,066
Are you out of your mind?

226
00:10:32,306 --> 00:10:33,505
Stupid woman!

227
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,426
You're a stupid woman!

228
00:11:09,585 --> 00:11:10,946
You finally answered the phone.

229
00:11:11,865 --> 00:11:14,386
I need to know what exactly happened.

230
00:11:16,225 --> 00:11:17,705
Just tell me what you can say.

231
00:11:21,585 --> 00:11:22,225
What?

232
00:11:23,465 --> 00:11:24,585
Shen Mo flipped the table?

233
00:11:27,546 --> 00:11:28,306
Okay, I got it.

234
00:11:28,306 --> 00:11:28,806
Thanks.

235
00:11:57,546 --> 00:11:58,546
What's going on?

236
00:11:58,906 --> 00:12:00,426
Shen Mo returned 2,000 cases to me!

237
00:12:00,426 --> 00:12:01,985
I had the goods ready in my warehouse.

238
00:12:01,985 --> 00:12:03,465
They're piled up, unable to ship out.

239
00:12:03,585 --> 00:12:04,266
What's wrong?

240
00:12:05,426 --> 00:12:06,666
I didn't expect

241
00:12:06,666 --> 00:12:09,186
that Shen Mo owned those small stores.

242
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:11,400
Usually, the primary distributors
supply the secondary,

243
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:14,066
the secondary supply the tertiary,
and then the retail stores.

244
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:14,825
I didn't expect

245
00:12:14,825 --> 00:12:16,345
that he, as a primary distributor,

246
00:12:16,666 --> 00:12:17,985
would actually open stores,

247
00:12:17,985 --> 00:12:20,066
small, unremarkable stores.

248
00:12:21,585 --> 00:12:24,225
It's basically trying
to have his cake and eat it too.

249
00:12:24,465 --> 00:12:25,186
Shameless!

250
00:12:25,186 --> 00:12:26,946
Didn't you know they've been doing this?

251
00:12:26,946 --> 00:12:28,186
I didn't know!

252
00:12:28,985 --> 00:12:31,186
Besides, Peter told me
to check it out at the meeting.

253
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:32,946
And you said yes too.

254
00:12:32,946 --> 00:12:33,985
Peter is my boss.

255
00:12:33,985 --> 00:12:35,465
If he says yes, how could I say no?

256
00:12:35,465 --> 00:12:36,666
Why didn't you remind me?

257
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:38,066
Am I obligated to remind you?

258
00:12:46,546 --> 00:12:47,146
I'm sorry.

259
00:12:47,585 --> 00:12:48,705
I decided to risk it myself.

260
00:12:56,488 --> 00:12:58,465
The relation
between a brand and its distributors

261
00:12:58,465 --> 00:12:59,745
is like a tightrope.

262
00:13:01,186 --> 00:13:03,345
Salespersons walk that tightrope
every single day.

263
00:13:03,546 --> 00:13:04,745
We need the distributors

264
00:13:05,225 --> 00:13:06,426
to help us meet our targets.

265
00:13:06,426 --> 00:13:08,666
But we can't rely solely on them either,

266
00:13:09,585 --> 00:13:11,345
because then
the profits won't be enough.

267
00:13:12,825 --> 00:13:14,306
It's true that we really want to know

268
00:13:14,306 --> 00:13:15,465
about the actual sales.

269
00:13:15,906 --> 00:13:18,865
But every time we try to find out,
it has to be done with extreme caution.

270
00:13:20,066 --> 00:13:21,946
I thought you understood this principle.

271
00:13:22,306 --> 00:13:23,186
I do understand!

272
00:13:24,705 --> 00:13:26,306
I just didn't grasp it deeply.

273
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:28,306
Then you shouldn't
have been the Sales Director.

274
00:13:28,705 --> 00:13:29,585
I'm sorry?

275
00:13:37,306 --> 00:13:38,105
I mean,

276
00:13:39,066 --> 00:13:40,666
sales isn't as simple as you think.

277
00:13:40,666 --> 00:13:41,705
If you think sales

278
00:13:41,985 --> 00:13:44,105
is just about selling wine
and dealing with clients,

279
00:13:44,306 --> 00:13:46,666
then you're not qualified
to be the Sales Director!

280
00:14:03,266 --> 00:14:04,266
(I never expected)

281
00:14:04,745 --> 00:14:07,026
(that Dong Yue could be so harsh.)

282
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:09,266
(But he was right.)

283
00:14:09,946 --> 00:14:11,066
(I oversimplified things.)

284
00:14:11,786 --> 00:14:15,465
(I was so eager to impress Peter
that I made such a rookie mistake.)

285
00:14:16,066 --> 00:14:17,066
(As for Peter,)

286
00:14:17,345 --> 00:14:18,585
(thinking back now,)

287
00:14:18,745 --> 00:14:21,386
(he deliberately dug a pit
for me to jump into.)

288
00:14:22,146 --> 00:14:23,266
(But ultimately,)

289
00:14:23,505 --> 00:14:25,546
(direct sales is my weakness.)

290
00:14:25,745 --> 00:14:29,105
(I shouldn't have fought them
in their own domain.)

291
00:14:31,505 --> 00:14:33,225
(Healthy)
(I should play to my strengths.)

292
00:14:41,786 --> 00:14:42,585
Rich.

293
00:14:43,306 --> 00:14:44,066
What a coincidence!

294
00:14:44,146 --> 00:14:44,786
Lu Xiaobai!

295
00:14:45,465 --> 00:14:47,266
You're out running this late too.

296
00:14:47,286 --> 00:14:47,786
Yeah.

297
00:14:47,786 --> 00:14:49,426
No time during the day. I have to work.

298
00:14:49,906 --> 00:14:50,705
How's your foot?

299
00:14:51,066 --> 00:14:52,066
Much better.

300
00:14:52,345 --> 00:14:53,825
How long do you run each time?

301
00:14:53,985 --> 00:14:55,705
Usually about 45 minutes.

302
00:14:55,705 --> 00:14:56,386
It depends.

303
00:14:57,345 --> 00:14:58,705
Will you work after running?

304
00:14:59,465 --> 00:14:59,965
Sure.

305
00:15:00,465 --> 00:15:01,345
Oh, my God.

306
00:15:01,946 --> 00:15:03,105
I have to.

307
00:15:03,105 --> 00:15:04,105
Strong woman.

308
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:12,130
(Rongrong)

309
00:15:14,345 --> 00:15:16,345
Rongrong, what's up?

310
00:15:16,426 --> 00:15:18,465
Fang got into a fight. Go there now!

311
00:15:18,465 --> 00:15:19,465
I'll come over later too.

312
00:15:19,465 --> 00:15:21,306
What? Where is she?

313
00:15:24,186 --> 00:15:24,906
Fang.

314
00:15:27,465 --> 00:15:28,306
Fang.

315
00:15:29,186 --> 00:15:30,186
Sorry.

316
00:15:33,186 --> 00:15:33,985
Fang.

317
00:15:34,465 --> 00:15:35,585
Sorry.

318
00:15:36,985 --> 00:15:37,786
Fang.

319
00:15:38,906 --> 00:15:39,705
Fang.

320
00:15:39,705 --> 00:15:40,465
Fang.

321
00:15:41,105 --> 00:15:41,946
Who are you?

322
00:15:42,426 --> 00:15:43,105
Sorry.

323
00:15:43,105 --> 00:15:44,105
Zixuan.

324
00:15:46,705 --> 00:15:47,906
Fang.

325
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:51,345
Let me see.

326
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:52,465
Does it hurt?

327
00:15:52,465 --> 00:15:53,306
It hurts.

328
00:15:54,546 --> 00:15:55,306
Poor thing.

329
00:15:55,306 --> 00:15:56,705
Let's go home.

330
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:57,505
I'm so scared.

331
00:15:57,505 --> 00:15:58,186
Go home.

332
00:15:58,186 --> 00:15:59,465
Don't be afraid.

333
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:01,546
I asked around for you.

334
00:16:02,026 --> 00:16:03,625
They're interested in your proposal.

335
00:16:04,345 --> 00:16:05,505
Let's meet up later.

336
00:16:06,066 --> 00:16:07,946
Great! That's wonderful.

337
00:16:08,345 --> 00:16:09,186
See you later then.

338
00:16:10,066 --> 00:16:11,306
Okay, bye.

339
00:16:12,345 --> 00:16:13,186
Ms. Zhao,

340
00:16:13,705 --> 00:16:16,906
last night,
a Wilson promoter had two people

341
00:16:17,306 --> 00:16:18,266
beat Fang up.

342
00:16:18,985 --> 00:16:19,825
What?

343
00:16:20,946 --> 00:16:21,825
Badly?

344
00:16:21,906 --> 00:16:23,306
Zixuan took care of her yesterday.

345
00:16:23,306 --> 00:16:24,666
Zixuan, come here.

346
00:16:26,345 --> 00:16:27,345
Fang was beaten?

347
00:16:27,345 --> 00:16:29,906
Her forehead was hit hard.
Needed several stitches.

348
00:16:30,066 --> 00:16:31,225
Is she still in the hospital?

349
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:33,505
No, I took her back to the dorm.

350
00:16:34,426 --> 00:16:35,105
Should we

351
00:16:35,105 --> 00:16:36,266
report this to HR?

352
00:16:40,426 --> 00:16:41,066
Yes.

353
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:43,705
We should report it.

354
00:16:44,786 --> 00:16:45,906
But not now.

355
00:16:46,705 --> 00:16:47,946
We just made one mistake.

356
00:16:47,946 --> 00:16:49,026
Can't afford another.

357
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:51,186
Wang Hao.

358
00:16:51,705 --> 00:16:52,745
You go check on Fang.

359
00:16:52,946 --> 00:16:54,625
Buy some good nutritional supplements.

360
00:16:55,825 --> 00:16:56,946
Tell Fang

361
00:16:58,306 --> 00:16:59,666
that the company knows.

362
00:16:59,946 --> 00:17:01,946
We're negotiating with Wilson now.

363
00:17:01,946 --> 00:17:03,465
We'll get justice for her.

364
00:17:04,346 --> 00:17:05,666
Tell her to rest and recover.

365
00:17:05,985 --> 00:17:06,985
Got it. I'll go now.

366
00:17:12,225 --> 00:17:13,305
Aren't you going?

367
00:17:15,106 --> 00:17:16,985
I will. I'll definitely go.

368
00:17:22,065 --> 00:17:24,386
(Fang, I heard you got hurt.)

369
00:17:24,985 --> 00:17:26,826
(Are you okay? I'll go see you later.)

370
00:17:31,650 --> 00:17:33,858
(Transfer to Fang: 2000 yuan)

371
00:17:44,785 --> 00:17:46,346
Ms. Zhao transferred me 2,000 yuan.

372
00:17:46,946 --> 00:17:47,906
That's good, isn't it?

373
00:17:48,826 --> 00:17:50,426
So it's handled?

374
00:17:51,225 --> 00:17:53,186
I barely slept last night.

375
00:17:54,065 --> 00:17:55,656
The more I thought, the worse I felt.

376
00:17:56,106 --> 00:17:57,186
It's so disheartening.

377
00:18:03,025 --> 00:18:03,906
I want to go home.

378
00:18:04,606 --> 00:18:05,106
Home?

379
00:18:05,106 --> 00:18:06,186
How long will you stay?

380
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:09,305
Fang.

381
00:18:09,686 --> 00:18:10,186
Strange.

382
00:18:10,186 --> 00:18:11,166
What's going on?

383
00:18:12,025 --> 00:18:12,705
Fang.

384
00:18:13,666 --> 00:18:14,265
Fang.

385
00:18:15,705 --> 00:18:18,225
This morning,
I checked with all relevant parties.

386
00:18:18,586 --> 00:18:20,826
Everyone agrees
that, as a liquor company,

387
00:18:20,985 --> 00:18:23,826
taking the lead
in promoting reasonable drinking

388
00:18:24,305 --> 00:18:25,505
shows great responsibility.

389
00:18:25,985 --> 00:18:27,785
I believe
the government will support it too.

390
00:18:29,065 --> 00:18:30,305
But it involves money.

391
00:18:31,106 --> 00:18:33,065
The Promotions Department
will cover the cost.

392
00:18:33,586 --> 00:18:36,465
I envision GST
spearheading this initiative,

393
00:18:36,465 --> 00:18:38,065
having Barry be the ambassador,

394
00:18:38,065 --> 00:18:41,146
and inviting other companies
and peers to join.

395
00:18:42,426 --> 00:18:43,586
Then it'll be much easier.

396
00:18:44,285 --> 00:18:46,626
In that case,
I can introduce you to some friends.

397
00:18:47,225 --> 00:18:48,186
With their help,

398
00:18:48,946 --> 00:18:49,745
it'll be simple.

399
00:18:50,785 --> 00:18:51,586
That's fantastic.

400
00:18:52,386 --> 00:18:53,265
Give me your address.

401
00:18:53,265 --> 00:18:54,426
I'll send you fine wine.

402
00:18:54,985 --> 00:18:56,106
I do love good wine.

403
00:18:56,705 --> 00:18:57,745
Thank you so much.

404
00:19:12,546 --> 00:19:15,554
(Reasonable Drinking Week Plan)

405
00:19:37,946 --> 00:19:39,946
I rang the doorbell to show my respect.

406
00:19:40,906 --> 00:19:42,386
You should've rung it downstairs.

407
00:19:43,426 --> 00:19:45,025
What if you didn't let me come up?

408
00:19:48,666 --> 00:19:50,705
What is it now? I'm busy.

409
00:19:52,465 --> 00:19:54,866
I heard you offended Shen Mo.

410
00:19:55,465 --> 00:19:56,465
At the office,

411
00:19:56,946 --> 00:19:57,985
he flipped a table over.

412
00:19:58,866 --> 00:20:01,745
He was just putting on a show
for my boss,

413
00:20:02,225 --> 00:20:03,545
acting out how furious he was.

414
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:06,386
It was nothing serious, just bluffing.

415
00:20:07,426 --> 00:20:09,426
Bluffing still makes a difference.

416
00:20:10,225 --> 00:20:11,225
Need my help?

417
00:20:11,626 --> 00:20:12,225
No.

418
00:20:13,225 --> 00:20:14,346
I already have a plan.

419
00:20:15,225 --> 00:20:16,465
Reasonable drinking?

420
00:20:21,426 --> 00:20:23,186
So you're boosting Barry's image?

421
00:20:24,906 --> 00:20:25,426
Yes.

422
00:20:26,465 --> 00:20:27,985
I can't win Shen Mo back.

423
00:20:28,465 --> 00:20:30,946
I can only try
to change Barry's opinion of me.

424
00:20:31,265 --> 00:20:33,225
Barry just wants to get re-appointed.

425
00:20:34,426 --> 00:20:36,106
Then he needs to prove his influence

426
00:20:36,106 --> 00:20:37,426
in China to headquarters

427
00:20:37,426 --> 00:20:40,906
and show how well-accepted he is
in the Chinese market.

428
00:20:40,946 --> 00:20:41,545
Smart.

429
00:20:42,505 --> 00:20:45,866
But GST alone
won't make enough difference.

430
00:20:48,386 --> 00:20:50,586
I've had several other companies
join the initiative.

431
00:20:51,146 --> 00:20:52,586
I'll help you get a few more.

432
00:20:52,586 --> 00:20:53,745
Count my company in.

433
00:20:53,745 --> 00:20:54,985
You don't need to do this.

434
00:20:55,346 --> 00:20:56,705
No, you don't need to do this.

435
00:20:57,186 --> 00:20:58,985
Besides being spouses,
we're friends, right?

436
00:20:59,586 --> 00:21:01,146
What's wrong with helping friends?

437
00:21:01,666 --> 00:21:03,745
If I needed your help at work,

438
00:21:03,946 --> 00:21:04,946
would you just stand by?

439
00:21:07,346 --> 00:21:08,906
Send me the plan once it's done.

440
00:21:09,586 --> 00:21:10,305
I have to go.

441
00:21:14,386 --> 00:21:15,666
You came all this way

442
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:17,225
just to tell me that?

443
00:21:17,545 --> 00:21:20,826
I heard about your trouble
and got worried about you.

444
00:21:21,745 --> 00:21:23,186
If you wanted to show concern,

445
00:21:23,186 --> 00:21:24,465
a phone call would've sufficed.

446
00:21:24,465 --> 00:21:26,186
Wouldn't that seem insincere?

447
00:21:26,745 --> 00:21:28,305
Alright, I'll go rally some people.

448
00:21:39,626 --> 00:21:40,426
No problem.

449
00:21:41,745 --> 00:21:43,186
I can fix this before eight.

450
00:21:45,586 --> 00:21:47,386
Yes, your time.

451
00:21:49,626 --> 00:21:50,785
Yes, I'm in office.

452
00:22:03,426 --> 00:22:06,434
(V. Conclusion)

453
00:22:19,490 --> 00:22:23,078
(Xiao Yang, Documents)

454
00:22:37,265 --> 00:22:37,946
Mr. Liu said

455
00:22:37,946 --> 00:22:38,985
our outline is fine,

456
00:22:38,985 --> 00:22:41,426
just make the details more concrete.

457
00:22:41,426 --> 00:22:42,065
That's all.

458
00:22:43,106 --> 00:22:44,505
Anyway, I think you can handle it.

459
00:22:44,505 --> 00:22:45,225
It's easy.

460
00:22:48,106 --> 00:22:49,785
Who's so sleepy?

461
00:22:51,186 --> 00:22:53,465
I get up at 5 AM every day now,

462
00:22:53,465 --> 00:22:55,346
do an hour on the elliptical,
have breakfast,

463
00:22:56,025 --> 00:22:57,225
and then head to work.

464
00:22:57,225 --> 00:22:58,426
It makes me full of energy.

465
00:23:30,946 --> 00:23:32,968
(Alarm: Good morning)

466
00:23:59,025 --> 00:24:00,866
All the info
for the project you're doing now

467
00:24:00,866 --> 00:24:03,346
is in this document.

468
00:24:03,866 --> 00:24:05,906
It's actually quite easy.

469
00:24:05,906 --> 00:24:08,106
Ask me if anything's unclear.

470
00:24:08,106 --> 00:24:08,626
Okay.

471
00:24:22,866 --> 00:24:23,826
I forgot something.

472
00:24:27,465 --> 00:24:28,146
Paperclips.

473
00:24:45,426 --> 00:24:46,146
Ma'am.

474
00:24:47,186 --> 00:24:48,866
Do you know where everyone went?

475
00:24:48,985 --> 00:24:49,906
I don't know.

476
00:25:02,265 --> 00:25:03,745
They're in Meeting Room 6.

477
00:25:04,106 --> 00:25:04,666
Thanks.

478
00:25:08,866 --> 00:25:09,586
Sorry, Mr. Xiao.

479
00:25:11,106 --> 00:25:12,305
I didn't get the notice.

480
00:25:19,946 --> 00:25:22,146
It's kind of last-minute.

481
00:25:22,666 --> 00:25:23,946
I'll go to the hospital later.

482
00:25:24,826 --> 00:25:25,666
Well,

483
00:25:26,826 --> 00:25:27,985
find yourself a seat.

484
00:25:30,426 --> 00:25:30,985
Go on.

485
00:25:32,426 --> 00:25:34,346
We've finished the initial phase
of the project.

486
00:25:34,346 --> 00:25:36,386
The latter phase needs your decisions.

487
00:25:41,586 --> 00:25:43,265
We've covered the project stuff.

488
00:25:44,745 --> 00:25:47,146
I've been hospitalized recently.
You've all worked hard.

489
00:25:48,426 --> 00:25:50,545
No empty gestures.
Here's something practical.

490
00:25:52,426 --> 00:25:53,946
Gift cards, one for each person.

491
00:25:55,146 --> 00:25:55,785
Pass them out.

492
00:25:57,265 --> 00:25:58,186
Very generous of you!

493
00:25:58,186 --> 00:25:59,946
- Thanks, Mr. Xiao!
- Thanks, Mr. Xiao!

494
00:25:59,946 --> 00:26:00,505
Here you are.

495
00:26:00,946 --> 00:26:02,146
Not at all.

496
00:26:02,146 --> 00:26:02,826
One per person.

497
00:26:03,186 --> 00:26:04,346
It's the least I could do.

498
00:26:07,386 --> 00:26:08,586
Look, guys,

499
00:26:08,906 --> 00:26:11,785
work is busy,
but you must balance work and rest.

500
00:26:13,386 --> 00:26:16,025
If anything is truly overwhelming,

501
00:26:16,386 --> 00:26:17,146
let me know.

502
00:26:19,346 --> 00:26:20,505
Colleagues

503
00:26:20,946 --> 00:26:22,265
can help each other out.

504
00:26:23,106 --> 00:26:23,666
Okay.

505
00:26:25,626 --> 00:26:26,906
Don't end up like me.

506
00:26:35,265 --> 00:26:36,426
I'd rather not sell.

507
00:26:37,096 --> 00:26:39,065
Mr. Lin, quite impressive!

508
00:26:39,586 --> 00:26:40,666
As you said,

509
00:26:40,666 --> 00:26:42,705
any customer ordering our liquor
in the store

510
00:26:42,705 --> 00:26:44,745
spends over 1,000 just on barbecue.

511
00:26:45,025 --> 00:26:47,225
Other stores can't even
attract such customers.

512
00:26:47,225 --> 00:26:49,065
And you're turning them away, Mr. Lin?

513
00:26:50,745 --> 00:26:52,106
Didn't I explain this to you?

514
00:26:52,265 --> 00:26:53,866
For a place like ours,

515
00:26:54,106 --> 00:26:56,985
our operating budget is pretty low.

516
00:26:57,426 --> 00:27:00,225
It's almost spent
on vegetables, seafood,

517
00:27:00,225 --> 00:27:02,106
and staff salaries,

518
00:27:02,106 --> 00:27:03,426
not much left.

519
00:27:03,426 --> 00:27:06,065
We genuinely can't afford
to buy imported liquor by the case.

520
00:27:06,065 --> 00:27:08,186
But consignment isn't sustainable.

521
00:27:08,186 --> 00:27:09,745
You know that too, right?

522
00:27:10,626 --> 00:27:11,265
To be honest,

523
00:27:12,186 --> 00:27:14,505
if it weren't
for your low-end liquor selection,

524
00:27:14,545 --> 00:27:16,186
the company wouldn't have allowed that.

525
00:27:16,545 --> 00:27:17,346
If you disagree,

526
00:27:18,745 --> 00:27:19,985
what about Wilson?

527
00:27:21,626 --> 00:27:22,186
Exactly.

528
00:27:22,785 --> 00:27:24,505
Wilson Black Knight.

529
00:27:24,985 --> 00:27:27,265
Their premium brandy
tastes excellent too.

530
00:27:27,265 --> 00:27:28,505
Nonsense!

531
00:27:29,025 --> 00:27:30,785
Black Knight mixed with herbal tea?

532
00:27:30,785 --> 00:27:32,946
Tastes like the slop water
from your kitchen.

533
00:27:32,946 --> 00:27:33,946
Tastes good?

534
00:27:34,346 --> 00:27:35,906
Are you kidding me?

535
00:27:37,265 --> 00:27:38,545
Come on, bottoms up!

536
00:27:38,545 --> 00:27:39,305
Penalty shot!

537
00:27:39,305 --> 00:27:40,025
Come on.

538
00:27:45,106 --> 00:27:46,025
Pour me another one.

539
00:27:47,265 --> 00:27:48,745
I'll have them open another bottle.

540
00:27:49,666 --> 00:27:50,826
Wilson!

541
00:27:53,386 --> 00:27:54,065
Handsome!

542
00:27:54,505 --> 00:27:55,005
What's up?

543
00:27:57,946 --> 00:27:59,745
Bring a 25-year-old bottle to my room.

544
00:28:00,426 --> 00:28:01,065
Got it.

545
00:28:01,065 --> 00:28:01,565
Come here.

546
00:28:08,465 --> 00:28:09,426
Serve them liquor.

547
00:28:09,426 --> 00:28:10,586
Just give me a soft drink.

548
00:28:11,386 --> 00:28:14,186
Those two drink like fish.

549
00:28:14,186 --> 00:28:15,225
I can't keep up with them.

550
00:28:15,465 --> 00:28:16,146
Understood.

551
00:28:19,745 --> 00:28:21,705
Your demand for imported liquor is low.

552
00:28:21,705 --> 00:28:22,826
I know that.

553
00:28:23,225 --> 00:28:24,785
But after this period,

554
00:28:25,186 --> 00:28:27,705
we actually track our daily sales.

555
00:28:27,705 --> 00:28:28,866
We know exactly.

556
00:28:29,225 --> 00:28:31,305
Liquor doesn't spoil or expire.

557
00:28:31,505 --> 00:28:32,785
What's there to fear?

558
00:28:33,465 --> 00:28:34,586
Even in the worst case,

559
00:28:34,586 --> 00:28:36,106
if it doesn't sell,

560
00:28:36,106 --> 00:28:38,265
no problem, you can resell it

561
00:28:38,265 --> 00:28:39,586
at the best price.

562
00:28:40,065 --> 00:28:42,666
Our liquor is blue-chip in the market.

563
00:28:42,666 --> 00:28:44,025
You both know this.

564
00:28:44,666 --> 00:28:47,386
I genuinely think you're impressive.

565
00:28:47,946 --> 00:28:49,106
Your drinking capacity,

566
00:28:49,906 --> 00:28:52,265
among all women I've met,

567
00:28:52,906 --> 00:28:54,146
is the highest.

568
00:28:55,545 --> 00:28:56,785
Until now,

569
00:28:57,985 --> 00:28:59,465
your face hasn't even flushed.

570
00:29:00,146 --> 00:29:01,785
Alcohol doesn't make me flush.

571
00:29:02,505 --> 00:29:03,305
No.

572
00:29:04,265 --> 00:29:05,505
Not only that,

573
00:29:05,586 --> 00:29:07,025
it's like you're stone-cold sober.

574
00:29:08,265 --> 00:29:09,745
How could I not be drinking?

575
00:29:09,985 --> 00:29:11,505
Is your liquor fake?

576
00:29:11,505 --> 00:29:12,785
What if it is not?

577
00:29:16,545 --> 00:29:17,666
Sugar water!

578
00:29:20,025 --> 00:29:21,465
Messing with us, huh?

579
00:29:21,465 --> 00:29:22,065
Alright.

580
00:29:22,745 --> 00:29:25,736
I can make a special request
to the company.

581
00:29:25,832 --> 00:29:27,826
If you could pay cash for the stock,

582
00:29:27,826 --> 00:29:30,586
how about
I get you an exclusive discount?

583
00:29:32,745 --> 00:29:34,705
Since you put it that way,

584
00:29:35,705 --> 00:29:37,745
if you lick every drop
of liquor on the table,

585
00:29:37,745 --> 00:29:39,305
no, sugar water,

586
00:29:40,025 --> 00:29:40,906
to be precise,

587
00:29:41,745 --> 00:29:44,265
I'll take that special discount.

588
00:29:44,426 --> 00:29:45,666
Cash on delivery.

589
00:29:48,025 --> 00:29:49,146
So will I.

590
00:29:51,586 --> 00:29:52,985
Are you serious,

591
00:29:52,985 --> 00:29:54,346
you two?

592
00:29:54,505 --> 00:29:55,946
You're fooling us.

593
00:29:56,025 --> 00:29:57,305
We're not playing tricks,

594
00:29:57,705 --> 00:29:58,505
but you are.

595
00:29:58,826 --> 00:30:01,666
We keep our word.

596
00:30:01,906 --> 00:30:02,826
Yeah.

597
00:30:19,778 --> 00:30:22,056
(Shen Mo)

598
00:30:29,545 --> 00:30:30,065
What's up?

599
00:30:32,186 --> 00:30:33,146
You're at my mom's shop?

600
00:30:33,785 --> 00:30:34,826
Why are you there?

601
00:30:40,785 --> 00:30:42,505
Fine. Just you wait.

602
00:30:47,505 --> 00:30:48,265
Listen,

603
00:30:49,065 --> 00:30:51,065
I won't lick the liquor.

604
00:30:52,465 --> 00:30:53,705
But I did make a mistake.

605
00:30:53,705 --> 00:30:54,906
Let me apologize first.

606
00:30:55,946 --> 00:30:57,785
I genuinely couldn't drink today.

607
00:30:58,106 --> 00:31:00,586
You saw it. Shen Mo just called me.

608
00:31:00,946 --> 00:31:02,505
Actually, today...

609
00:31:06,065 --> 00:31:07,186
I won't elaborate.

610
00:31:07,906 --> 00:31:08,826
But

611
00:31:08,826 --> 00:31:11,106
if you are willing
to give me a chance to make amends,

612
00:31:11,106 --> 00:31:12,705
I'll set up another gathering next time.

613
00:31:12,705 --> 00:31:14,225
I'll definitely drink with you

614
00:31:14,225 --> 00:31:16,065
even if I'm vomiting blood.

615
00:31:16,065 --> 00:31:17,465
I'll make you satisfied, okay?

616
00:31:18,106 --> 00:31:19,225
So, apologies for today.

617
00:31:19,225 --> 00:31:20,745
I have to go.

618
00:31:20,985 --> 00:31:22,225
I need to go find Mr. Shen.

619
00:31:24,545 --> 00:31:28,225
You're going to see Shen Mo?

620
00:31:28,785 --> 00:31:30,666
Yes, Shen Mo.

621
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:34,265
Since you've apologized,

622
00:31:34,265 --> 00:31:36,426
we will just let it go.

623
00:31:36,785 --> 00:31:38,826
What kind of discount do we get?

624
00:31:40,906 --> 00:31:41,505
Five percent.

625
00:31:42,586 --> 00:31:43,505
Five percent.

626
00:31:43,505 --> 00:31:45,785
Plus, I can apply
for a one-percent sales rebate

627
00:31:45,785 --> 00:31:47,745
for you two.

628
00:31:48,785 --> 00:31:49,906
Other stores don't have it.

629
00:31:50,785 --> 00:31:51,666
It's just for you two.

630
00:31:57,465 --> 00:31:58,465
Okay, I accept it.

631
00:31:59,545 --> 00:32:01,465
So do I.

632
00:32:01,465 --> 00:32:02,225
Okay.

633
00:32:02,666 --> 00:32:03,305
Okay?

634
00:32:03,305 --> 00:32:04,505
Okay.

635
00:32:05,025 --> 00:32:06,545
I'm not just boasting,

636
00:32:07,265 --> 00:32:09,465
but you won't find beef balls this good

637
00:32:09,465 --> 00:32:11,225
anywhere else in Guangzhou.

638
00:32:11,346 --> 00:32:12,586
- I've heard about it.
- Mom.

639
00:32:15,745 --> 00:32:16,305
Mr. Jin.

640
00:32:16,666 --> 00:32:17,225
Ms. Liang.

641
00:32:17,745 --> 00:32:19,225
Why are you alone? Where's Shen Mo?

642
00:32:19,785 --> 00:32:21,186
Mr. Shen is parking outside.

643
00:32:24,305 --> 00:32:26,505
Ms. Liang, I am truly sorry.

644
00:32:26,745 --> 00:32:28,946
Today, I'll get straight to the point.

645
00:32:30,465 --> 00:32:33,146
What happened before
was entirely my wife's fault.

646
00:32:33,465 --> 00:32:36,065
As her husband,
I'm also undeniably responsible.

647
00:32:36,745 --> 00:32:39,826
Today, I came specifically
to offer my sincere apology to you.

648
00:32:40,985 --> 00:32:43,106
Additionally,
I'd like to place a small order.

649
00:32:43,505 --> 00:32:44,545
I hope you'll accept it.

650
00:32:58,586 --> 00:32:59,505
Thank you.

651
00:32:59,505 --> 00:33:00,225
Not at all.

652
00:33:06,225 --> 00:33:06,725
Mr. Jin.

653
00:33:07,705 --> 00:33:08,705
I accept your apology.

654
00:33:09,106 --> 00:33:10,346
But forget about the order.

655
00:33:10,826 --> 00:33:13,265
Your company has been blacklisted
by ours.

656
00:33:13,265 --> 00:33:14,866
I can't do business with you anymore.

657
00:33:15,985 --> 00:33:17,505
What's between us is settled.

658
00:33:18,426 --> 00:33:19,745
Unless it's necessary,

659
00:33:19,745 --> 00:33:20,906
we don't need to meet again.

660
00:33:21,265 --> 00:33:22,346
Well, listen...

661
00:33:22,346 --> 00:33:23,346
Bye, I won't see you out.

662
00:33:38,985 --> 00:33:40,904
Is he the man
who sent the fish maw and abalone?

663
00:33:40,904 --> 00:33:42,265
No. He's my client.

664
00:33:42,586 --> 00:33:45,626
It's better he's not.
He's way too old anyway.

665
00:33:45,946 --> 00:33:47,545
If you need money, ask me.

666
00:33:47,545 --> 00:33:48,505
Can't find a bad man.

667
00:33:48,505 --> 00:33:50,426
I know.

668
00:33:50,505 --> 00:33:51,005
You...

669
00:33:52,265 --> 00:33:54,186
I kindly offered her a deal,

670
00:33:54,426 --> 00:33:55,386
but she just refused.

671
00:33:56,106 --> 00:33:57,465
She practically kicked me out.

672
00:33:58,025 --> 00:33:59,025
I can't deal with her.

673
00:34:00,146 --> 00:34:00,646
Here she is.

674
00:34:05,906 --> 00:34:08,665
I was only gone
for five minutes and got a ticket.

675
00:34:09,266 --> 00:34:10,346
Is this your car?

676
00:34:11,105 --> 00:34:11,706
A new car.

677
00:34:13,665 --> 00:34:14,760
Let's talk somewhere else.

678
00:34:15,585 --> 00:34:18,145
Since I've got the ticket,
parking a bit longer won't matter.

679
00:34:18,706 --> 00:34:20,545
I don't want people to watch.

680
00:34:23,386 --> 00:34:24,485
Alright, get in.

681
00:34:46,185 --> 00:34:46,786
Wait.

682
00:34:47,906 --> 00:34:50,866
Was it necessary
to get Jin Linsheng to apologize to me?

683
00:34:51,505 --> 00:34:52,065
Yes, it was.

684
00:34:53,226 --> 00:34:54,465
I also need to apologize.

685
00:34:56,145 --> 00:34:57,145
For what?

686
00:34:57,426 --> 00:34:58,746
I heard you lost orders.

687
00:34:59,946 --> 00:35:00,746
So you're behind it,

688
00:35:00,746 --> 00:35:02,025
aren't you?

689
00:35:02,226 --> 00:35:02,985
No.

690
00:35:04,585 --> 00:35:07,025
But I admit it happened because of me.

691
00:35:08,065 --> 00:35:09,185
At the dinner that night,

692
00:35:09,946 --> 00:35:12,226
everyone asked
why I hadn't brought you along.

693
00:35:12,906 --> 00:35:13,866
I told them the truth.

694
00:35:15,025 --> 00:35:18,025
You told them
that I was being ungrateful?

695
00:35:19,185 --> 00:35:20,185
Did someone tell you?

696
00:35:23,426 --> 00:35:24,025
I'm sorry.

697
00:35:25,105 --> 00:35:26,505
I've been quite angry these days.

698
00:35:26,906 --> 00:35:28,746
You cursed me out and broke up with me.

699
00:35:29,786 --> 00:35:30,946
I was a bit upset.

700
00:35:33,266 --> 00:35:34,185
See?

701
00:35:34,426 --> 00:35:36,946
You get a little upset,
and someone punishes me on your behalf.

702
00:35:37,065 --> 00:35:38,866
It proves
I wasn't wrong to curse you out.

703
00:35:39,306 --> 00:35:40,105
I didn't mean it.

704
00:35:40,105 --> 00:35:42,786
Anyway, the result is what it is.

705
00:35:43,226 --> 00:35:45,946
What are you, the "emperor"?

706
00:35:46,065 --> 00:35:46,866
Your one word

707
00:35:46,866 --> 00:35:48,266
made me lose clients.

708
00:35:48,746 --> 00:35:49,585
What did I do to you?

709
00:35:49,585 --> 00:35:50,706
I just broke up with you.

710
00:35:51,665 --> 00:35:52,746
What exactly did you lose?

711
00:35:53,065 --> 00:35:54,946
What great favor
did I ever get from you?

712
00:35:55,426 --> 00:35:56,306
I had meals with you.

713
00:35:56,306 --> 00:35:56,985
I played golf

714
00:35:56,985 --> 00:35:58,025
for your business.

715
00:35:58,426 --> 00:36:00,105
I was even in love with you.

716
00:36:00,145 --> 00:36:01,306
You don't need to say that.

717
00:36:01,306 --> 00:36:03,185
I never did anything to hurt you, right,

718
00:36:03,185 --> 00:36:05,226
Mr. Shen?

719
00:36:05,665 --> 00:36:07,306
One good turn deserves another.

720
00:36:07,306 --> 00:36:08,465
You're a father yourself.

721
00:36:08,465 --> 00:36:09,665
Do some good deeds!

722
00:36:14,665 --> 00:36:16,328
I kicked your car, and you glared at me.

723
00:36:16,946 --> 00:36:18,185
Am I in for more bad luck?

724
00:36:18,706 --> 00:36:20,826
Oh, my God, I'm so scared.

725
00:36:20,985 --> 00:36:22,585
Oh, right, you're the "emperor".

726
00:36:22,585 --> 00:36:23,720
Nobody dares kick your car.

727
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:25,224
Nobody dares talk to you like this.

728
00:36:25,346 --> 00:36:26,426
I'll resign soon.

729
00:36:26,625 --> 00:36:28,706
This is Guangzhou.
Cameras are everywhere.

730
00:36:28,866 --> 00:36:30,386
You want to kill me, go ahead.

731
00:36:32,346 --> 00:36:33,346
I was wrong.

732
00:36:34,226 --> 00:36:35,625
Heaven has punished me too.

733
00:36:36,545 --> 00:36:37,426
Punished you?

734
00:36:37,426 --> 00:36:39,226
Punished you with a 200-yuan ticket?

735
00:36:40,946 --> 00:36:42,306
I have severe heart disease.

736
00:36:48,786 --> 00:36:50,866
It showed up in my physical a year ago.

737
00:36:52,985 --> 00:36:54,056
Hardening of the arteries.

738
00:36:55,346 --> 00:36:56,346
And some dissection.

739
00:36:57,585 --> 00:36:58,226
I can't

740
00:36:59,065 --> 00:36:59,946
remember the details.

741
00:37:00,665 --> 00:37:01,736
It's been acting up again.

742
00:37:03,065 --> 00:37:05,145
The doctors gave me an ultimatum.

743
00:37:05,946 --> 00:37:07,025
I need a stent.

744
00:37:08,185 --> 00:37:08,746
I may also

745
00:37:09,545 --> 00:37:10,786
need a mechanical valve.

746
00:37:13,386 --> 00:37:15,226
Are you playing a trick again?

747
00:37:15,625 --> 00:37:16,866
No, I'm not.

748
00:37:17,786 --> 00:37:19,145
I believe in Feng Shui.

749
00:37:19,625 --> 00:37:20,985
I wouldn't jinx myself.

750
00:37:26,706 --> 00:37:27,706
How did it happen?

751
00:37:29,065 --> 00:37:29,665
I don't know.

752
00:37:31,185 --> 00:37:32,426
Maybe too much drinking.

753
00:37:33,145 --> 00:37:35,346
Or doing too many bad things.
Probably both.

754
00:37:37,665 --> 00:37:38,665
Although it's serious,

755
00:37:39,585 --> 00:37:41,426
experts think it can still be treated.

756
00:37:41,906 --> 00:37:42,706
Don't worry.

757
00:37:45,185 --> 00:37:46,545
I don't worry about you.

758
00:37:46,985 --> 00:37:48,625
Technology is so advanced now.

759
00:37:48,786 --> 00:37:50,145
You'll recover quickly, for sure.

760
00:37:53,306 --> 00:37:54,185
I hope so.

761
00:37:56,386 --> 00:37:58,226
I'll have the surgery
by the end of the month.

762
00:37:59,426 --> 00:38:01,185
I've already told a few friends of mine

763
00:38:01,866 --> 00:38:03,306
not to misunderstand

764
00:38:05,065 --> 00:38:07,065
and asked them to support your work.

765
00:38:08,625 --> 00:38:11,426
And regarding the new VIP client policy,

766
00:38:12,826 --> 00:38:14,145
actually, it was Barry's idea.

767
00:38:15,025 --> 00:38:18,306
He wants key accounts controlled
by the company,

768
00:38:19,145 --> 00:38:21,386
not by individual top salespeople.

769
00:38:21,786 --> 00:38:22,706
That's all.

770
00:38:23,025 --> 00:38:24,145
He asked for my support.

771
00:38:25,105 --> 00:38:26,505
I backed him without thinking much.

772
00:38:27,465 --> 00:38:28,706
He wasn't targeting you.

773
00:38:29,985 --> 00:38:31,226
No need to explain. I get it.

774
00:38:34,906 --> 00:38:35,985
The point is,

775
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:37,665
can we

776
00:38:40,226 --> 00:38:41,346
not break up?

777
00:38:44,426 --> 00:38:46,105
This might sound shameless,

778
00:38:46,826 --> 00:38:47,326
but

779
00:38:49,505 --> 00:38:50,226
my illness

780
00:38:50,985 --> 00:38:51,746
made me realize

781
00:38:53,386 --> 00:38:54,025
I might be...

782
00:38:57,426 --> 00:38:58,505
I really am getting old.

783
00:39:00,826 --> 00:39:02,826
I can't live a lonely life anymore.

784
00:39:03,625 --> 00:39:04,625
I want a partner.

785
00:39:06,346 --> 00:39:07,105
You're the one

786
00:39:08,266 --> 00:39:09,266
I trust the most.

787
00:39:13,226 --> 00:39:14,786
I admit the things you scolded me for,

788
00:39:15,985 --> 00:39:18,706
and I'll change.

789
00:39:22,426 --> 00:39:25,105
Please don't abandon me. Okay?

790
00:39:34,465 --> 00:39:35,866
I can't give you an answer

791
00:39:36,505 --> 00:39:38,185
right now.

792
00:39:41,105 --> 00:39:41,786
I understand.

793
00:39:42,826 --> 00:39:44,306
No rush. Take your time.

794
00:39:46,145 --> 00:39:46,706
Well...

795
00:39:48,866 --> 00:39:49,906
Let me drive you back.

796
00:40:13,426 --> 00:40:14,145
I'll drive.

797
00:40:15,906 --> 00:40:17,025
Let me get you home first.

798
00:40:18,185 --> 00:40:20,065
Don't drive yourself
until after the surgery.

799
00:40:20,786 --> 00:40:22,665
You make it sound like
I told you on purpose.

800
00:40:23,306 --> 00:40:25,625
Of course.
You totally did it on purpose.

801
00:40:25,906 --> 00:40:27,112
Give me the key. I'll drive.

802
00:40:29,866 --> 00:40:31,786
This is a 300-horsepower car.
You can't drive.

803
00:40:32,946 --> 00:40:34,065
I can.

804
00:40:34,465 --> 00:40:36,065
I took a two-week course on the track.

805
00:40:38,025 --> 00:40:39,025
I remember you said

806
00:40:39,585 --> 00:40:40,866
you would pay

807
00:40:41,105 --> 00:40:43,226
to learn anything your client likes.

808
00:40:44,025 --> 00:40:46,906
You really are a jack of all trades.

809
00:40:47,105 --> 00:40:48,465
Stop buttering me up.

810
00:40:48,505 --> 00:40:49,185
Get in.

811
00:40:51,505 --> 00:40:52,426
You still can't drive.

812
00:40:54,065 --> 00:40:55,145
You just drank.

813
00:40:56,025 --> 00:40:56,706
Oh, right!

814
00:41:00,145 --> 00:41:01,505
How did you know I drank?

815
00:41:01,946 --> 00:41:03,065
Someone told you again?

816
00:41:03,505 --> 00:41:05,786
You've got way too many informants.

817
00:41:07,585 --> 00:41:08,746
I just happened to see it.

818
00:41:26,203 --> 00:41:30,943
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

819
00:41:35,393 --> 00:41:37,313
♪Too much of shame♪

820
00:41:37,659 --> 00:41:40,455
♪To waste it crying♪

821
00:41:42,913 --> 00:41:44,833
♪Leave all behind you♪

822
00:41:44,833 --> 00:41:47,113
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

823
00:41:47,233 --> 00:41:49,462
♪You know how far you've gone♪

824
00:41:49,597 --> 00:41:51,873
♪In the fire you rise again♪

825
00:41:52,059 --> 00:41:54,419
♪You made it through the worst♪

826
00:41:54,557 --> 00:41:56,761
♪The best is yet to come♪

827
00:41:57,004 --> 00:41:59,144
♪The best is yet to come♪

828
00:42:01,846 --> 00:42:03,169
♪Isn't it magical♪

829
00:42:03,169 --> 00:42:04,801
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

830
00:42:04,833 --> 00:42:07,300
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

831
00:42:07,300 --> 00:42:09,753
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

832
00:42:09,834 --> 00:42:12,482
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

833
00:42:12,571 --> 00:42:15,102
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

834
00:42:15,182 --> 00:42:17,404
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

835
00:42:17,546 --> 00:42:18,627
♪But I don't want to♪

836
00:42:18,736 --> 00:42:21,002
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

837
00:42:21,118 --> 00:42:22,183
♪Until 3 AM♪

838
00:42:22,354 --> 00:42:23,559
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

839
00:42:23,713 --> 00:42:24,946
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

840
00:42:25,037 --> 00:42:27,401
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

841
00:42:27,548 --> 00:42:31,958
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

842
00:42:46,683 --> 00:42:48,119
♪Leave all behind you♪

843
00:42:48,223 --> 00:42:50,710
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

844
00:42:50,893 --> 00:42:53,022
♪You know how far you've gone♪

845
00:42:53,209 --> 00:42:55,549
♪In the fire you rise again♪

846
00:42:55,617 --> 00:42:57,883
♪You made it through the worst♪

847
00:42:58,243 --> 00:43:00,321
♪The best is yet to come♪

848
00:43:00,570 --> 00:43:02,740
♪The best is yet to come♪

849
00:43:05,441 --> 00:43:06,593
♪Isn't it magical♪

850
00:43:06,593 --> 00:43:10,239
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

851
00:43:10,273 --> 00:43:12,129
♪And I see them sparkling♪

852
00:43:12,353 --> 00:43:14,484
♪Nobody knows♪

853
00:43:15,105 --> 00:43:17,015
♪What tomorrow brings♪

854
00:43:17,281 --> 00:43:19,604
♪You made it through the worst♪

855
00:43:19,791 --> 00:43:21,999
♪The best is yet to come♪

856
00:43:22,286 --> 00:43:24,435
♪The best is yet to come♪

857
00:43:24,731 --> 00:43:26,145
♪Isn't it magical♪

858
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:28,357
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

859
00:43:28,431 --> 00:43:30,785
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

860
00:43:30,785 --> 00:43:31,873
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

861
00:43:31,873 --> 00:43:35,324
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

862
00:43:35,777 --> 00:43:38,051
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

863
00:43:38,465 --> 00:43:39,329
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

864
00:43:39,329 --> 00:43:40,849
♪Isn't it magical♪
